my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) The BBQ appliance should be placed on deck and clear of all combustible and flammable material; 
b) Under no circumstances should the BBQ appliance be left unattended when lit; 
c) Portable fire extinguisher to be on stand-by, adjacent to the BBQ; 
d) The BBQ should be extinguished as soon as the food has been prepared; 
e) The BBQ appliance should be sheltered from the wind to prevent hot ash and sparks from being blown on deck; 
f) Hot ash must be extinguished and disposed off in accordance with MARPOL regulations.

a) Crew to have knowledge on how to safely use, empty and clean the BBQ appliance; 
b) Use of appropriate PPE: long sleeve t-shirts, heat-resistant gloves, cloths and aprons; 
c) The BBQ appliance should be cordoned off (i.e. guard rope) to prevent any unnecessary crew coming in to contact with hot surfaces.
